# Paraul, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Paraul (; , Pari-avul) is a rural locality (a selo) in Karabudakhkentsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 4,949 as of 2010. There are 66 streets.
Geography
Paraul is located 90&nbsp;km northwest of Novokayakent (the district's administrative centre) by road. Karabudakhkent and Buynaksk are the nearest rural localities.
